<body class="body">
  <div class="container wrapper">
    <br />

    <br />
    <h2 class="text-center text-info">Caption Rater - The Game!</h2>
    <p class="text-center">
      You will be presented with a series of images, along with a caption that
      describes the image. Rate how well the caption fits the image using the
      guide provided.
    </p>

    <p class="text-center">
      Before you begin the game, you will need to successfully complete a
      tutorial. First, you will rate 10 images to familiarize yourself with the
      game and the rating system. Then, you will complete 25 ratings without
      feedback.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-center text-info">Rating Guide</h2>
    <p class="text-center">
      This guide is available to you during gameplay. Please use it as necessary
      to ensure the most accurate ratings!
    </p>
    <div id="myDIV">
      <table class="table table-bordered table-secondary table-responsive">
        <thead class="thead-light">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Rating</th>
            <th scope="col">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">1</th>
            <td>
              Objects are incorrectly identified. The caption gives the wrong
              idea about what is happening in the image.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">2</th>
            <td>
              Objects are partially correctly identified with some errors. The
              caption is giving an idea of what is happening in the image There
              is no interpretation of what anything means.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">3</th>
            <td>
              Relevant objects are correctly identified. The caption describes
              what is seen but not where objects are in space. There is no
              description of the overall setting and no interpretation of an
              event.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">4</th>
            <td>
              Objects and/or a general scene and/or an action are correctly
              identified but not every element is completely identified. The
              caption describes what is seen and where things are in space.
              There is no interpretation of an event.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">5</th>
            <td>
              Objects, a general scene, and actions are correctly identified if
              present in the image. The caption describes what is seen and where
              things are in space.
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <br />

    <h2 class="text-center text-info">Examples</h2>
    <p class="text-center">
      Use the following rating examples to guide your ratings.
    </p>
    <img
      class="image"
      src="https://caption.click/gifs/1131932671_c8d17751b3.jpg"
    />
    <table class="table table-bordered table-secondary table-responsive">
      <thead>
        <tr class="tableizer-firstrow">
          <th>Caption</th>
          <th>Rating/Explanation</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>A woman plays guitar by a round light</td>
          <td>
            1 - A viewer would have a completely wrong understanding of the
            image. 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>A child jumping on a tennis court</td>
          <td>
            2 - A viewer would have a partial understanding of the objects in
            the image and no understanding of the scene, context, or actions in
            the image. 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>A child is jumping in a room </td>
          <td>
            3 - A viewer would understand what objects are in the image but
            unable to identify the scene, context, or actions that are in the
            image.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>A child jumps on a bed</td>
          <td>
            4 - A viewer would understand what objects are in the image but only
            able to partially identify some part of the scene, context, or
            actions that are in the image.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>A boy jumps from one bed to another</td>
          <td>
            5 - A viewer would accurately understand the objects, and accurately
            and completely identify the scene, context, and actions that are in
            the image. 
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <br />
    <img
      class="image"
      src="https://caption.click/gifs/127488876_f2d2a89588.jpg"
    />
    <table class="table table-bordered table-secondary table-responsive">
      <thead>
        <tr class="tableizer-firstrow">
          <th>Caption</th>
          <th>Rating/Explanation</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>A dog jumps over an obstacle</td>
          <td>
            1 - A viewer would have a completely wrong understanding of the
            image. 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>A dog in a grassy field, looking up</td>
          <td>
            2 - A viewer would have a partial understanding of the objects in
            the image and no understanding of the scene, context, or actions in
            the image. 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Two people in a grassy field with trees</td>
          <td>
            3 - A viewer would understand what objects are in the image but
            unable to identify the scene, context, or actions that are in the
            image.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Two people stand in a grassy field looking at trees</td>
          <td>
            4 - A viewer would understand what objects are in the image but only
            able to partially identify some part of the scene, context, or
            actions that are in the image.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Two golfers stand in a grassy field looking towards trees</td>
          <td>
            5 - A viewer would accurately understand the objects, and accurately
            and completely identify the scene, context, and actions that are in
            the image. 
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <br />

    <form method="GET" action="/tutorial" class="form-group">
      <input
        class="button_next"
        type="submit"
        name="submit"
        class="button_next"
        value="Next"
      />
    </form>
  </div>
